layout.p:
Columns: 147;
                                                  ruled lines: 57 58;
                                                  written lines: 57 58; Uniform layout. Ruling by hard point.Visible pricking and stitching. 147 columns in total, two to four columns per membrane. Three tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on אבדהחיספקת. The letters ש  and צ sometimes provided with four tagin, and ט and צ sometimes with five tagin. The letters בהכךמםספףקת occasionally with three tagin, and on הכמפר sometimes two. The letter ח arched throughout. Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. Special shapes of the letter  ו, נ, פ, ע, ח, ז, י, ל, ס, ר occur. The inverted נ before and after Num. 10:35-36 is missing. The "puncta extraordinaria" placed on the words fixed by masorah. Wooden rollers (870mm high).
